He sighed, laid the handbag aside and added in the same tone of voice: 'Yes, the most respectable German players. And one Austrian.

My late papa was unlucky. He hoped there would be no real interest in chess here and we landed right in a tournament.'

Things had been rebuilt and jumbled, the wing of the house now looked different. They had lived over there, on the second floor. It had been decided to stay until the end of the year and then return to Russia

